{
  "stem": "7506.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The barrack describes one building, and there are various barracks, of course.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the camp, Belsen, was a camp that had different departments within it, all known as Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were in one barrack, and that barrack was number 17.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the barrack-- the part of the camp where that barrack was known at that time as the Sternlager, Sternlager meaning the camp with the stars.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But as I said, there were other parts of the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Bergen-Belsen was a camp that was built before the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It started to be built before the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it is built-- And it was built near a German army camp which existed from a long time before the war outside the village of Bergen.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The camp, that army camp, still exists today, to this day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So outside of the army camp was begun before the war, Haftlingslager, a prisoner's camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in that camp originally were Russians, or communist sympathizers, collected up since Hitler came to power in 1933.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Anyone that didn't go accords to the Nazi doctrine was against the state.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And therefore, a lot of them were either executed or put into different camps all over Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And one of those camps was Belsen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The part where we were was constructed for us mostly, not for communist sympathizers but for Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But the Jews that went to Belsen, Belsen camp for the Jews, was not as the other camps are known, [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Belsen was an [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And [GERMAN] for people that could be used by the Nazi regime for benefit, such as [GERMAN], exchange, for beneficial things for the Nazi regime.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There were in Belsen people with dual nationality, similar to my mothers and my aunts being born in England.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
